"v.逗留，留恋 【英】 v. 逗留，留恋(to continue to stay) 【记】 ling(可能来自length 长度)+er→拉长(时间 )→逗留 【例】 Smoke lingered long after the fire was extinguished. v. (因不愿离开而)逗留, 留恋 【记】ling = long, er－拉长时间－逗留 【记】源自long + er；length + er 延长；line + er 一条线延长 linger (v.)  c.1300, lenger ""reside, dwell,"" northern England frequentative of lengen ""to tarry,"" from Old English lengan ""prolong, lengthen,"" from Proto-Germanic *langjan ""to make long"" (cognates: Old Frisian lendza, Old High German lengan, Dutch lengen ""to lengthen""), source of Old English lang (see long (adj.)). Sense of ""delay going, depart slowly and unwillingly"" is from 1520s. Related: Lingered; lingering."
